  "diff_vs_948_assistant": "FINDING: chatglm.cn root (/) auto-redirects to /main/alltoolsdetail and uses the SAME endpoint family as the /main/alltoolsdetail UI: POST https://chatglm.cn/chatglm/backend-api/assistant/stream with a hardcoded default assistant_id=65940acff94777010aa6b796 (the 'general' assistant). There is NO separate '/chatglm/mainchat-api/.../stream' chat endpoint for anonymous root chat — mainchat-api is only used for conversation list (/conversation/recent_list, /conversation/title) and status (/guest/chat_status, /stream/update_status). DIFF vs #948: #948 hit the same /chatglm/backend-api/assistant/stream URL with a SPECIFIC (non-default) assistant_id (an /alltoolsdetail-selected assistant). #956 hits it with the DEFAULT assistant_id (general chat) reached by anonymous root navigation. Conclusion: APF block/warning matching on path /chatglm/backend-api/assistant/stream covers BOTH cases. The assistant_id in request body distinguishes general-chat vs specific-tool sessions but the streaming wire protocol is identical.",
  "secondary_endpoints_observed": [
    "POST /chatglm/mainchat-api/conversation/recent_list (conversation list)",
    "GET  /chatglm/mainchat-api/conversation/title?conversation_id=... (title fetch/generation)",
    "GET  /chatglm/mainchat-api/guest/chat_status (anonymous quota/status)",
    "POST /chatglm/mainchat-api/stream/update_status (stream lifecycle ping)"
  ]
